        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 5:47PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Edinburg North High
School to Olivarez to near Ratamosa. Movement was south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Edinburg, Weslaco, Donna, Mercedes, Elsa, Edcouch, La Villa, Edinburg
Regional Medical Center, Weslaco Mid Valley Airport, and Llano Grande
Country Club.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
